  h2#precursor 1. Before you start
  :marked
    You'll need to have a recent XCode on your machine for Homebrew to work.

    1. Install XCode from the App Store. (Takes a while.)
    2. Open XCode once so you can accept the licence agreement. Then close it again.

  h2#install 2. Install Homebrew
  :marked
    Visit [brew.sh](http://brew.sh/) and follow the instructions.

    After installing, your system will now have the `brew` command. This makes it easy to install other tools like [Node.js](/software/node/).

