  h2#cask 3. Install Homebrew Cask
  :marked
    This is a useful extension to Homebrew. While the `brew` command is generally for installing command line tools, `brew cask` is for installing Mac apps like Chrome, Sublime Text 3, etc. This is often much easier than manually downloading and installing apps from their websites or from the App Store.

    To install:
    
    ```sh
    $ brew install caskroom/cask/brew-cask
    ```

    

    Now you can install Mac apps with a simple command, like this:

    ```sh
    $ brew cask install sublime-text3
    ```

    The apps are kept in a central location managed by Cask, and then symlinked from your `~/Applications` folder.
    
    More information: [caskroom.io](http://caskroom.io/)

    Search for available apps: [caskroom.io/search](http://caskroom.io/search)
